<plot>What if you died because your hospital considered you an expendable commodity? Today's health care costs are at an all-time high, and malpractice rates are climbing steadily. Yet some hospitals are making a fortune at patients' expense. The results are deadly, yet no one is being held accountable. Affected individuals -from patients to top level health care officials- speak out about the corruption, exposing the sinister side of health care in this dramatic lively expose.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?335719</url></doc>
